8
00:00:25,734 --> 00:00:28,361
to upstage
my kindergarten graduation speech.

9
00:00:28,945 --> 00:00:31,906
But I'm not gonna let you get in my way,
not this time.

10
00:00:33,825 --> 00:00:35,493
God, do I detest you.

11
00:00:36,244 --> 00:00:39,622
I loathe you, Bennett Russell.
I despise you, Bennett Russell.

12
00:00:39,706 --> 00:00:41,586
- I abhor you...
- [man] Isn't that right, Lona?

13
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:43,001
I'm sorry?

14
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:46,421
Isn't your president
usually decided by a vote?

15
00:00:46,504 --> 00:00:49,591
Yes, but since we have an even number
of members, we cannot have a vote.

16
00:00:49,674 --> 00:00:51,843
- Well, how many members do you have?
- Two.

17
00:00:52,427 --> 00:00:54,637
- Uh, she and I.
- Her and I.

18
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:57,599
- Her and myself.
- Him and me, myself and I. We, two!

19
00:00:57,682 --> 00:00:58,826
- I got it.
- [Bennett] He gets it.

20
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:00,494
[Lona] Therefore,
seniority should take precedent.

21
00:01:00,518 --> 00:01:03,563
- I'm a month older than she is.
- No, seniority, not age.

22
00:01:03,646 --> 00:01:06,083
I've participated and placed
in more total events than he has,

23
00:01:06,107 --> 00:01:07,025
including the state tournament.

24
00:01:07,108 --> 00:01:09,569
I've also raised more money
than she has for our program,

25
00:01:09,652 --> 00:01:11,738
and for our school
and for that lovely building...

26
00:01:11,821 --> 00:01:14,341
You don't get to buy your way
to the top with your mother's Rolodex.

27
00:01:14,365 --> 00:01:17,452
Isn't this ultimately
Mr. Johnson's responsibility?

28
00:01:17,535 --> 00:01:18,535
Absolutely.

29
00:01:18,578 --> 00:01:21,664
But he said that if he made the decision,
it would cause tension in our club.

30
00:01:21,748 --> 00:01:24,209
- Principal Nelson, this is our...
- Co-presidents!

31
00:01:24,292 --> 00:01:25,292
Co what?

32
00:01:25,794 --> 00:01:27,587
Co-presidents!

33
00:01:27,670 --> 00:01:29,464
Therefore, unlike years past,

34
00:01:29,547 --> 00:01:31,716
the two of you will finally learn
how to work together.

35
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:34,844
No! Co-presidents goes against the purpose
of even having a president.

36
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:35,970
Fine. No president.

37
00:01:36,054 --> 00:01:37,054
No president?

38
00:01:37,096 --> 00:01:40,475
No president, co-president,
I don't give a damn.

39
00:01:40,558 --> 00:01:43,394
A year from now,
I'm gonna be in the south of France,

40
00:01:43,478 --> 00:01:48,274
