to wipe their butts
with any type of currency.

117
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:04,489
Mr. Johnson, it's a terrible site.

118
00:06:04,572 --> 00:06:07,134
We only get to buy a subscription
to one research database per year,

119
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:09,202
and it should be East Law.
It's ranked number one.

120
00:06:09,285 --> 00:06:11,746
- By you and your mom?
- By U.S. News Report.

121
00:06:11,829 --> 00:06:13,509
And besides,
we have to conserve our funds,

122
00:06:13,581 --> 00:06:15,976
so that Taylor and Tucker
have the resources they need to learn.

123
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:16,834
Who?

124
00:06:16,918 --> 00:06:19,587
Taylor and Tanner
joined our club this afternoon.

125
00:06:20,588 --> 00:06:22,799
[Lona]
And they deserve to have an opinion.

126
00:06:22,882 --> 00:06:25,802
Democracy is democracy.
It doesn't matter if they're uneducated.

127
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:27,696
- [Mr. Johnson] New. She means new.
- Same difference.

128
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,638
She means new.

129
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:30,973
We don't even know
what a research database is.

130
00:06:31,057 --> 00:06:32,558
You both are going to do great.

131
00:06:32,642 --> 00:06:35,120
[Mr. Johnson] Now, first of all,
this team needed some new faces,

132
00:06:35,144 --> 00:06:36,896
and apparently a new attitude.

133
00:06:36,979 --> 00:06:39,357
Second of all,
if we're gonna get anywhere this year,

134
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:42,318
you two have gotta agree
on something, anything,

135
00:06:42,401 --> 00:06:44,779
or I swear
I'm gonna make the twins co-presidents.

136
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:50,576
Bennett said he raised money?
Am I to assume he went door to door?

137
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:54,205
'Cause his mother's an ATM with lipstick
who releases 50s every time she farts.

138
00:06:54,288 --> 00:06:56,082
She's a very popular senator.

139
00:06:56,165 --> 00:06:57,583
- Please.
- [man speaking on TV]

140
00:06:58,167 --> 00:07:00,336
- Julia's a state senator.
- [scoffs]

141
00:07:00,503 --> 00:07:03,172
And to me, she's still the teenage robot
who lived in the library.

142
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:04,507
Hey! I live in the library.

143
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:06,801
- Yeah, you're different.
- Different how?

144
00:07:07,468 --> 00:07:08,594
You're just different.

145
00:07:09,178 --> 00:07:11,472
Listen, tomorrow you're gonna win
another trophy

146
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:13,975
and the Harvard application
isn't due for another week...

147
00:07:14,058 --> 00:07:15,058
Four days.

148
00:07:16,185 --> 00:07:17,520
Shit! Four days?

149
00:07:19,021 --> 00:07:20,440
Okay, well, did you write it in?

150
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:23,067
Yes. Lona Skinner, co-president...

151
00:07:23,151 --> 00:07:25,236
...of the Hemlock Prep Academy
Debate Club.

152
00:07:25,319 --> 00:07:27,572
You should be proud of that.

153
00:07:27,655 --> 00:07:28,489
- [breathes out]
- What?

154
00:07:28,573 --> 00:07:33,327
You earned it, and you are qualified,
and you are my son.

155
00:07:33,411 --> 00:07:36,038
[cell phone ringing]

156
00:07:37,039 --> 00:07:38,416
One second, baby.

157
00:07:38,499 --> 00:07:39,499
Julia Russell.

158
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:45,756
Listen, I was in D.C. last week.
I'm going to D.C. next week,

159
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:51,137
so you tell those wrinkled old bags
that I am not coming to D.C. this week,

160
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:54,765
and if they lose their shit
I will buy each of them a diaper.

161
00:08:00,229 --> 00:08:04,525
As a first-generation college student,
I know the importance of higher education,

162
00:08:04,609 --> 00:08:08,279
which is why I started this foundation
that hands out scholarships.

163
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:10,781
I'm hanging up on you now.

164
00:08:10,865 --> 00:08:11,908
Sorry, baby.

165
00:08:11,991 --> 00:08:14,452
No, it's just that
being co-presidents is ridiculous,

166
00:08:14,535 --> 00:08:16,454
- because Lona is impossible to work with.
- Oh!

167
00:08:16,537 --> 00:08:18,372
Forget about her and her mother.

168
00:08:18,456 --> 00:08:22,084
You just need to focus
on that good-looking dude in the mirror

169
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:24,629
that's getting into Yale. Am I right?

170
00:08:24,712 --> 00:08:28,257
[woman] Right? Next month,
you'll qualify for the state tournament

171
00:08:28,341 --> 00:08:31,511
and Harvard will give you a full ride,
just like Hemlock did.

172
00:08:31,594 --> 00:08:32,887
Because we're poor.

173
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:36,516
No. Because you're smart.

174
00:08:37,099 --> 00:08:39,018
And you're a hard worker.

175
00:08:39,101 --> 00:08:41,229
And you're a kick-ass debater.

176
00:08:43,105 --> 00:08:44,899
[sighs] And because we're poor.

177
00:08:44,982 --> 00:08:47,109
I'm just glad it'll all be over soon.

178
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:49,987
I'll be at Harvard and Bennett
will be at Yale, and that will be that.

179
00:08:51,113 --> 00:08:52,114
