Do you... Do you think I want this?

742
00:37:26,702 --> 00:37:28,462
- [scoffs] I certainly don't.
- Neither do I.

743
00:37:28,537 --> 00:37:29,681
Out of everyone in this school,

744
00:37:29,705 --> 00:37:31,785
you're literally the last person
I want to work with.

745
00:37:31,832 --> 00:37:34,460
- The very, very last.
- Thank you.

746
00:37:34,543 --> 00:37:36,671
You're egocentric,
you speed through crossfire

747
00:37:36,754 --> 00:37:38,339
and you refuse to flow rounds.

748
00:37:40,341 --> 00:37:41,884
I flow every single one of my rounds.

749
00:37:41,968 --> 00:37:45,096
And for your information,
when you speed through crossfire,

750
00:37:45,179 --> 00:37:47,574
you get through more questions
and you make the other team nervous.

751
00:37:47,598 --> 00:37:49,517
No, I think you're right,
we wouldn't qualify.

752
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:52,061
- You're just not good enough.
- Oh, please.

753
00:37:52,144 --> 00:37:54,414
I could carry us both through qualifiers
and state championship.

754
00:37:54,438 --> 00:37:56,416
- You think we'd win?
- Yeah, if you got out of my way.

755
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:57,316
- Prove it.
- I will.

756
00:37:57,400 --> 00:38:00,420
So it's agreed. You'll prove me wrong,
we'll play as a team, qualify next month,

757
00:38:00,444 --> 00:38:01,612
and win the state tournament.

758
00:38:01,696 --> 00:38:03,531
We'll start studying after school
at my place.

759
00:38:04,156 --> 00:38:05,700
[indistinct chattering]

760
00:38:09,036 --> 00:38:10,746
[birds chirping]

761
00:38:10,830 --> 00:38:12,224
[Bennett] I'll give the opening statement.

762
00:38:12,248 --> 00:38:14,583
No, I'm gonna give the opening statement.

763
00:38:14,667 --> 00:38:16,395
Bennett, the round is one
of the first five minutes.

764
00:38:16,419 --> 00:38:19,171
You make too many arguments
and don't impact any of them.

765
00:38:19,255 --> 00:38:22,008
So we lose the round because of that.
In addition to that...

766
00:38:22,091 --> 00:38:23,735
[Lona] If you did your work
for the amount of time

767
00:38:23,759 --> 00:38:25,696
- you spend arguing with me...
- I'm already done.

768
00:38:25,720 --> 00:38:27,930
I'm already done.
I already finished page two.

769
00:38:28,014 --> 00:38:31,142
- [Lona] Well, start page three.
- [Bennett] There is no page three.

770
00:38:34,687 --> 00:38:36,522
[Bennett] No. No.

771
00:38:36,605 --> 00:38:37,606
- No, no.
- Stop.

772
00:38:37,690 --> 00:38:38,524
[Bennett] Excuse me.

773
00:38:38,607 --> 00:38:39,483
- [Lona] What?
- No.

774
00:38:39,567 --> 00:38:42,254
Ask any teacher, they will tell you
that when you write something physically,

775
00:38:42,278 --> 00:38:44,715
it sticks to your brain better
than when you do it on your computer.

776
00:38:44,739 --> 00:38:47,366
[Bennett] Excuse me. Thank you.

777
00:38:47,450 --> 00:38:49,428
- Condescending tone?
- Which the judges do not appreciate.

778
00:38:49,452 --> 00:38:51,912
And besides,
it sets the tone for the entire round.

779
00:38:51,996 --> 00:38:55,583
My judges appreciate my tone.
I have a very welcoming tone.

780
00:38:55,666 --> 00:38:58,794
[Bennett and Lona speaking rapidly]

781
00:39:10,014 --> 00:39:11,182
[sighs]

782
00:39:15,436 --> 00:39:17,730
[Lona] Okay, enough, Picasso.
I'll make these last changes

783
00:39:17,813 --> 00:39:19,482
- and email them to you.
- Or I can do it.

784
00:39:19,565 --> 00:39:21,484
- No, I can do it.
- I can easily do it.

785
00:39:21,567 --> 00:39:23,819
Yeah, you can easily do
a lot of things, Bennett.

786
00:39:24,403 --> 00:39:25,696
[sighs]

787
00:39:25,780 --> 00:39:27,740
Look, I'll make the changes
and see you tomorrow.

788
00:39:29,492 --> 00:39:30,576
We're gonna do great.

789
00:39:31,827 --> 00:39:33,245
[door closes]

790
00:39:33,329 --> 00:39:34,705
[alarm ringing]

791
00:39:34,789 --> 00:39:35,789
[sighs]

792
00:39:40,378 --> 00:39:43,214
I know I've said it a thousand times,
but I really am sorry.

793
00:39:43,798 --> 00:39:45,758
- It's fine, Mom.
- No, it's not.

794
00:39:45,841 --> 00:39:48,469
I let Julia get under my tits,
and then I made it worse.

795
00:39:48,552 --> 00:39:50,888
If I had just kept
my hilarious mouth shut,

796
00:39:50,971 --> 00:39:52,611
you would've already qualified for State.

797
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:54,100
Or maybe I just lost that day.

798
00:39:54,183 --> 00:39:56,936
Are you kidding me? Did you see
how stupid some of those kids were?

799
00:39:58,229 --> 00:39:59,229
Talented.

800
00:40:00,356 --> 00:40:01,356
In their own way.

801
00:40:03,442 --> 00:40:06,195
Whoa! Take it easy with that stuff.
They won't even recognize you.

802
00:40:06,278 --> 00:40:07,822
[groans]

803
00:40:07,905 --> 00:40:09,698
Look, I'm just... I'm flustered, okay?

804
00:40:09,782 --> 00:40:11,075
We have no chemistry.

805
00:40:11,158 --> 00:40:14,036
We disagree in strategy,
we have opposite routines and I just...

806
00:40:14,120 --> 00:40:15,454
I don't know how it's gonna work!

807
00:40:15,913 --> 00:40:16,747
[sighs]

808
00:40:16,831 --> 00:40:19,351
[Julia] I just wanted to tell you
that I spoke to the debate leadership

809
00:40:19,375 --> 00:40:20,793
on the county and state levels

810
00:40:20,876 --> 00:40:24,588
about Amy's primal impulses
and that unfortunate altercation.

811
00:40:24,672 --> 00:40:27,216
And they assured me
that I was in the right, of course,

812
00:40:27,299 --> 00:40:29,427
and that you would be judged fairly.

813
00:40:29,510 --> 00:40:31,429
- Whatever.
- Well... No.

814
00:40:31,512 --> 00:40:33,764
This is good news, Bennett.

815
00:40:35,474 --> 00:40:37,452
You are going to qualify
for the state tournament today

816
00:40:37,476 --> 00:40:40,229
and you are going to win
the state tournament.

817
00:40:40,312 --> 00:40:42,731
And you will go to Yale in the fall.

818
00:40:42,815 --> 00:40:44,876
But first, I have to compete
in the debate tournament

819
00:40:44,900 --> 00:40:47,236
with a brand new partner
whom I've hated my entire life.

820
00:40:47,319 --> 00:40:49,864
We all know who's carrying this team.

821
00:40:50,990 --> 00:40:52,241
Goodbye, Mom.

822
00:40:52,324 --> 00:40:54,160
[indistinct chattering]

